1
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:12,800
I heard you say you're only
pretending to be hurt

2
00:00:12,867 --> 00:00:14,400
to get Red's attention.

3
00:00:14,467 --> 00:00:15,967
It's not what you think.

4
00:00:16,033 --> 00:00:17,567
My legs still hurt...

5
00:00:17,633 --> 00:00:18,967
Stop it, Sabina!

6
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:21,267
Fine! My feet never hurt!

7
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:22,600
I was just pretending, yes!

8
00:00:22,667 --> 00:00:23,733
For Red!

9
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:25,500
Your lie should end now.

10
00:00:25,567 --> 00:00:26,633
I'm going to tell Red.

11
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:29,867
Do you know me to accuse me
like this?

12
00:00:29,933 --> 00:00:33,867
By doing that, what makes you
different from criminals?

13
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:37,467
Confront me if you can prove
that I killed someone

14
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:38,500
in this neighborhood!

15
00:00:38,567 --> 00:00:40,133
I won't fight you.

16
00:00:40,200 --> 00:00:41,433
As the Lord once said,

17
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,067
if someone throws a stone
at you...

18
00:00:43,133 --> 00:00:44,833
Don't you dare use
the word of God!

19
00:00:44,900 --> 00:00:47,167
Shove a rice cake down
her throat!

20
00:00:50,267 --> 00:00:52,967
Eden, we're back!

21
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:54,567
I don't think they're here.

22
00:00:54,633 --> 00:00:55,600
Where did they go?

23
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,233
Stay away from Red!

24
00:00:57,300 --> 00:00:59,033
Stay away from Red!

25
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,767
Stop!

26
00:01:03,467 --> 00:01:05,100
Yenyen!

27
00:01:05,167 --> 00:01:06,800
So, where did they go?

28
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:07,867
I don't know.

29
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,267
Sab can't walk.

30
00:01:09,333 --> 00:01:10,267
Her feet still hurt.

31
00:01:10,333 --> 00:01:11,633
I'm Rina Ramos.

32
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:13,467
I am the mother
of Roderick Ramos.

33
00:01:13,533 --> 00:01:15,100
Is there any news about him?

34
00:01:15,167 --> 00:01:16,067
Rina.

35
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:18,267
I talked to her first.

36
00:01:18,333 --> 00:01:20,767
And now you have the guts
to squeeze by?

37
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:24,267
You know, your opinion
does not matter.

38
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:25,633
Leave me alone, Sabina!

39
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:28,700
I won't do that because
you can't talk to Red!

40
00:01:28,767 --> 00:01:31,433
I won't let you ruin us!

41
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:35,133
Amanda, everything revolves
around money.

42
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:39,000
Too bad you don't have money.

43
00:01:39,067 --> 00:01:40,500
I tried to like you,

44
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:42,500
but I really couldn't force
myself.

45
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:44,033
Why don't we just accept it?

46
00:01:44,100 --> 00:01:46,333
Someone else deserves your love.

47
00:01:46,400 --> 00:01:49,400
And it's not me, Sab!

48
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:51,533
Red!

49
00:01:52,767 --> 00:01:53,867
Red!

50
00:01:55,767 --> 00:01:57,400
Red, no. Please.

51
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:01,333
You don't mean that.

52
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,500
You don't mean that.

53
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,133
- I'm sorry.
- Sorry.

54
00:02:19,333 --> 00:02:21,667
Let me apologize first...

55
00:02:23,067 --> 00:02:24,567
especially for what Sab
did to you.

56
00:02:24,633 --> 00:02:25,933
You got hurt.

57
00:02:28,033 --> 00:02:30,267
If only I listened
and believed you,

58
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,633
it wouldn't get to this point.

59
00:02:33,667 --> 00:02:36,900
So I'm sorry for
believing Sabina

60
00:02:36,967 --> 00:02:39,033
and falling into her schemes.

61
00:02:40,767 --> 00:02:42,833
Yen, I understand.

62
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:51,467
Now I've proven to myself
that I really like you.

63
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,733
You know...

64
00:02:56,900 --> 00:03:02,933
when I was with Sab,
I thought of nothing but you.

65
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,267
Just you.

66
00:03:06,333 --> 00:03:09,000
That's how sure I am
about my feelings for you, Yen.

67
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:19,567
I missed you so much.

68
00:03:19,633 --> 00:03:21,300
I missed you so much.

69
00:03:21,767 --> 00:03:23,100
I missed you.

70
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:29,133
I missed you too, Red.

71
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:33,367
I'm so afraid to let you go.

72
00:03:33,433 --> 00:03:35,467
I thought I would lose you.

73
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:39,100
I thought...

74
00:03:39,167 --> 00:03:41,633
if we wouldn't get
out of here...

75
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:44,767
if we couldn't go back
to Manila anymore...

76
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:51,067
I know that I'm with you.

77
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:56,367
I will still be happy.

78
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:01,900
Because I love you, Red.

79
00:04:04,733 --> 00:04:06,733
I love you so much.

80
00:05:23,667 --> 00:05:27,133
You should talk to Sabina,
so you could patch things up.

81
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,400
We've been on this island
for a long time now.

82
00:05:29,467 --> 00:05:30,233
At least if you're the one
who will talk to her,

83
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,100
maybe she will listen.

84
00:05:32,167 --> 00:05:34,067
I'll just look for Raichu.

85
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,267
Okay.

86
00:05:52,533 --> 00:05:53,733
Sab.

87
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:56,800
So are you mad at me now?

88
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,900
What will be our setup?

89
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:03,600
Are you and Yenyen
a couple now?

90
00:06:05,867 --> 00:06:07,533
What about me?

91
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:11,867
Sab, we can still be friends.

92
00:06:11,933 --> 00:06:14,033
That's not what I want.

93
00:06:15,700 --> 00:06:18,500
Red, I love you so much.

94
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:25,167
I can't even imagine myself
moving on without you.

95
00:06:27,133 --> 00:06:31,800
I can't bear it just thinking
about the idea of losing you.

96
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:42,167
Why? Why don't you tell me
where I fell short?

97
00:06:43,167 --> 00:06:44,633
I'll make it up to you.

98
00:06:44,700 --> 00:06:46,967
I'll do whatever it is
that you want.

99
00:06:47,033 --> 00:06:48,333
Anything.

100
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:50,967
Or...

101
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:56,900
tell me what Yenyen has
that I don't have.

102
00:06:57,933 --> 00:07:00,400
I will make the adjustments.

103
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:02,600
Just please, please.

104
00:07:02,667 --> 00:07:04,233
Please take me back, Red.

105
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:06,500
Please take me back again.

106
00:07:06,567 --> 00:07:08,200
Please.

107
00:07:10,867 --> 00:07:12,067
Sab...

108
00:07:12,133 --> 00:07:13,333
Sab, please.

109
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,600
Stop it.

110
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,433
Look at yourself.
Don't you feel bad for yourself?

111
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:22,033
Have some self-respect.

112
00:07:23,200 --> 00:07:25,967
Don't push for the things
that you can no longer have.

113
00:07:27,467 --> 00:07:29,733
All we need to do now is...

114
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,733
is just move forward.

115
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:34,700
What if I don't want to?

116
00:07:34,767 --> 00:07:37,500
You're just making it hard
for yourself.

117
00:07:37,567 --> 00:07:39,333
I can't do anything about it.

118
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,767
I'm sorry.

119
00:07:46,533 --> 00:07:47,700
Raichu!

120
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,733
Raichu!

121
00:07:51,633 --> 00:07:53,033
Raichu!

122
00:07:55,067 --> 00:07:56,400
Raichu!

123
00:07:58,233 --> 00:08:00,233
I hate to do this to you.

124
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:03,500
But if you don't have anything
left to say,

125
00:08:03,567 --> 00:08:05,900
I'll go follow Yenyen
and Raichu.

126
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,133
Wait, Red.

127
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,167
Red, do you see what I see?

128
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:12,167
Oh my God!

129
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:14,700
Hello, we're here!

130
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,467
There are rescuers!
Yenyen and Raichu need to know!

131
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:21,733
Hey! We're here!

132
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,167
Wait! Hey, Red, don't leave.

133
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:25,400
They might miss us if you leave.

134
00:08:25,467 --> 00:08:26,467
I need to tell Yenyen
and Raichu.

135
00:08:26,533 --> 00:08:28,400
Hold on!
We're here!

136
00:08:28,467 --> 00:08:29,767
Mister!

137
00:08:29,833 --> 00:08:30,800
Mister, we're here...

138
00:08:30,867 --> 00:08:31,900
Red!

139
00:08:31,967 --> 00:08:34,833
Red! Come on!

140
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,100
Red!

141
00:08:42,100 --> 00:08:43,733
Raichu!

142
00:08:45,033 --> 00:08:46,133
Raichu!

143
00:08:53,467 --> 00:08:54,700
Raichu!

144
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:58,500
Raichu!

145
00:09:00,300 --> 00:09:01,700
Raichu!

146
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:03,233
Yen!

147
00:09:33,700 --> 00:09:34,833
Yen!

148
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,067
Yenyen!

149
00:09:53,700 --> 00:09:54,633
This belongs to Yenyen.

150
00:09:54,700 --> 00:09:56,067
Red!

151
00:09:57,433 --> 00:09:58,700
Red, we have to go back.

152
00:09:58,767 --> 00:10:02,267
The rescuers might leave.

153
00:10:02,367 --> 00:10:05,133
I won't leave without Yenyen.

154
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:07,900
Why don't you just help me find
them so we can go back?

155
00:10:07,967 --> 00:10:10,233
What if the rescuers leave?

156
00:10:10,300 --> 00:10:14,633
- Red, this is our only chance.
- I won't leave without Yenyen.

157
00:10:23,367 --> 00:10:24,333
Eden!

158
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,133
Thank God, you're here.

159
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:28,300
Raichu!

160
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:30,667
This is our only chance.

161
00:10:30,733 --> 00:10:31,933
Yen!

162
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,167
Red!

163
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,300
Yen!

164
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:43,733
Red!

165
00:10:46,300 --> 00:10:48,433
What are you doing there?

166
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:49,533
I saw a snake.

167
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:52,567
So I ran and climbed up
this tree.

168
00:10:57,033 --> 00:10:58,533
Thank you, Eden.

169
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:00,500
Red! Oh my God!

170
00:11:00,567 --> 00:11:01,433
Red!

171
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,900
Red!

172
00:11:08,267 --> 00:11:09,600
Red!

173
00:11:09,667 --> 00:11:10,633
Red!

174
00:11:10,700 --> 00:11:11,933
Red, Red, wake up!

175
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,667
Wake up, wake up!

176
00:11:13,733 --> 00:11:14,833
Babe, wake up, please!

177
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:17,333
Please wake up!

178
00:11:17,400 --> 00:11:18,367
Oh my God!

179
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:19,933
Help!

180
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:22,467
Help! Help us!

181
00:11:22,533 --> 00:11:23,500
Help us, please!

182
00:11:23,567 --> 00:11:25,000
Babe, wake up! Please, wake up!

183
00:11:25,067 --> 00:11:27,167
Wake up! Wake up!

184
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,800
Help!

185
00:11:29,867 --> 00:11:31,733
Help! Help us!

186
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:34,033
Help us, please!

187
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:35,167
Help!

188
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,967
Help!

189
00:11:40,033 --> 00:11:41,733
Help! Babe, wake up!

190
00:11:41,833 --> 00:11:43,900
Wake up, wake up!

191
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:48,933
Mister!

192
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,433
Help!

193
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:55,933
Hurry up, please!

194
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:01,233
Babe, please.

195
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,367
Red.

196
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:04,200
Mister, help us.

197
00:12:04,267 --> 00:12:06,300
My boyfriend hit his head.

198
00:12:06,367 --> 00:12:07,867
Help us.

199
00:12:09,533 --> 00:12:10,833
- Come on, come on!
- Please, Mister.

200
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:11,900
Help us.

201
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:12,800
Here, here.

202
00:12:12,867 --> 00:12:15,067
His head is bleeding.

203
00:12:16,267 --> 00:12:17,667
Hurry up, please.

204
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,933
Are the two of you
plane crash survivors?

205
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,400
Yes.

206
00:12:24,467 --> 00:12:26,367
Are there other survivors here?

207
00:12:28,367 --> 00:12:30,033
No more.
It's just the two of us.

208
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:32,700
Please, let's bring him
to the hospital.

209
00:12:58,900 --> 00:12:59,900
Roger! Roger!

210
00:12:59,967 --> 00:13:02,800
We found two survivors
on the nearby island.

211
00:13:02,867 --> 00:13:04,000
One is injured.

212
00:13:04,067 --> 00:13:05,700
We're on our way back
to the headquarters.

213
00:13:06,633 --> 00:13:08,400
Please, let's hurry up.

214
00:13:08,467 --> 00:13:09,833
We're the only ones here.

215
00:13:09,900 --> 00:13:10,733
Please, Mister.

216
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,367
My boyfriend needs
to see a doctor.

217
00:13:12,433 --> 00:13:13,800
Please, Mister, please.

218
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:15,533
Let's hurry up.

219
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,933
Please, let's hurry up!

220
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:25,267
My gosh!

221
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:28,533
I thought I would die.

222
00:13:28,600 --> 00:13:30,567
What were you doing there?

223
00:13:30,633 --> 00:13:31,633
Where were you?

224
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,400
You were with Sabina again!

225
00:13:33,467 --> 00:13:35,200
Long story. Let's just go.

226
00:13:35,267 --> 00:13:37,033
Red might already be waiting
for us.

227
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,100
Come on.

228
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,000
Raichu!

229
00:14:04,067 --> 00:14:05,600
Do you hear that?

230
00:14:06,467 --> 00:14:07,800
It sounds like a boat.

231
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:13,900
I think a boat passed by.

232
00:14:13,967 --> 00:14:15,367
Come on! Let's go!

233
00:14:15,433 --> 00:14:18,100
Ouch!

234
00:14:22,533 --> 00:14:23,867
Go on. Go ahead.

235
00:14:23,933 --> 00:14:25,233
- My back hurts.
- No, I won't leave you here.

236
00:14:25,300 --> 00:14:26,567
- I'll be right behind you.
- We'll go together.

237
00:14:26,633 --> 00:14:28,200
Come on. Hold on to me.

238
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,100
I can't leave you here.
Let's go.

239
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:37,567
- It hurts.
- The boat's here.

240
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:39,600
Come on, you can do it.

241
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:52,967
Careful.

242
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:02,833
Eden.

243
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:03,867
Can you still go on?

244
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:05,933
Can you still walk?

245
00:15:07,133 --> 00:15:08,200
Here.

246
00:15:14,767 --> 00:15:17,133
You can do it.

247
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:20,033
- Ouch!
- Hey, hey.

248
00:15:25,767 --> 00:15:26,733
Here we are.

249
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:30,967
Raichu.

250
00:15:31,033 --> 00:15:32,100
Here.

251
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,533
Ouch.

252
00:15:41,333 --> 00:15:42,300
Right here.

253
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:45,833
Ouch.

254
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:47,267
There's the boat.

255
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,300
Red!

256
00:15:58,367 --> 00:15:59,533
Sabina!

257
00:16:01,833 --> 00:16:02,933
Sabina!

258
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,467
We're still here!

259
00:16:09,367 --> 00:16:10,967
Sabina!

260
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:24,633
We're still here!

261
00:16:29,767 --> 00:16:31,167
Red!

262
00:16:55,200 --> 00:16:56,567
Red!

263
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,633
Red!

264
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:06,833
Red!

265
00:17:06,900 --> 00:17:08,833
We're still here, Red!

266
00:17:08,900 --> 00:17:10,467
Red!

267
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:12,567
Sabina!

268
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,600
We're still here!

269
00:17:16,900 --> 00:17:17,900
Red!

270
00:17:18,967 --> 00:17:20,767
Come back!

271
00:17:21,433 --> 00:17:23,867
I still want to see my mom!

272
00:17:23,933 --> 00:17:26,467
- Red!
- We're still here!

273
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Red!

274
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,333
Raichu, they left us.

275
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:46,267
Red!

276
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:53,767
I have a feeling that
this is Sabina's doing.

277
00:17:53,833 --> 00:17:56,033
This is her fault.

278
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:57,267
No.

279
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,100
This can't be.
Red won't leave me.

280
00:18:00,167 --> 00:18:01,300
I know him.

281
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:05,033
Hold on.

282
00:18:05,100 --> 00:18:07,067
Why did he agree to leave?

283
00:18:07,133 --> 00:18:08,567
What happened to Red?

284
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,600
I don't know.

285
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:14,833
No, Eden.

286
00:18:14,900 --> 00:18:17,933
They left us like garbage.

287
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:20,067
No, Raichu!

288
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:21,900
He won't leave me.

289
00:18:22,000 --> 00:18:24,400
You had a talk already, right?

290
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:26,700
Everything's okay
between you two.

291
00:18:26,767 --> 00:18:30,200
But why did he leave us
like trash?

292
00:18:30,267 --> 00:18:31,500
Can it be...

293
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:32,800
He will come back for us.

294
00:18:32,867 --> 00:18:33,933
He won't leave us.

295
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,800
I believe in him.

296
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:38,767
He will come back for us.

297
00:18:39,500 --> 00:18:41,533
I will reunite with my mom.

298
00:18:42,433 --> 00:18:44,467
He'll come back for us.

299
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:46,500
He'll come back.

300
00:18:46,567 --> 00:18:48,300
I believe in Red.

301
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,433
He'll come back, right?

302
00:19:01,233 --> 00:19:03,067
What do we do now?

303
00:19:03,133 --> 00:19:05,000
We're the only ones here.

304
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:07,633
They don't care about us
anymore.

305
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:09,400
What are we going to do?

306
00:19:09,467 --> 00:19:11,267
No, Raichu.

307
00:19:11,333 --> 00:19:12,733
Red will come back.

308
00:19:14,667 --> 00:19:17,333
I know he will come back.
He promised me.

309
00:19:18,133 --> 00:19:19,667
Maybe something happened to him.

310
00:19:19,733 --> 00:19:21,667
I'm sure he'll come back.

311
00:19:23,133 --> 00:19:24,933
Seriously?

312
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,967
Do you really believe
they'll come back for us?

313
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,067
I know Red.

314
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:32,167
He'll come back for me.

315
00:19:32,233 --> 00:19:34,000
He won't leave me.

316
00:19:35,067 --> 00:19:36,167
He made a promise.

317
00:19:36,233 --> 00:19:41,833
He said he won't leave me
no matter what.

318
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:44,533
Eden...

319
00:19:45,700 --> 00:19:48,567
what if Sabina did something?

320
00:19:51,067 --> 00:19:54,233
Even so.

321
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:57,233
I know Red won't do that.

322
00:19:58,533 --> 00:20:00,467
He will come back for us.

323
00:20:00,533 --> 00:20:01,600
That's what he told me.

324
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,000
That's his promise.

325
00:20:03,067 --> 00:20:05,033
We'll wait for him.

326
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:08,167
We'll wait for him, okay?

327
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:10,100
They'll come back.

328
00:20:13,267 --> 00:20:15,167
If you say so.

329
00:20:22,767 --> 00:20:24,167
Excuse me.

330
00:20:24,233 --> 00:20:26,267
For the family of the
plane crash victims,

331
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:29,100
we received an update from the
headquarters of the rescue team.

332
00:20:29,167 --> 00:20:31,467
Two survivors are rescued.

333
00:20:31,533 --> 00:20:34,233
One female and one male.

334
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:37,233
Can we know their names?

335
00:20:37,300 --> 00:20:39,167
Who are they?

336
00:20:39,233 --> 00:20:40,267
What are their names?

337
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:43,700
Please, tell us.

338
00:20:43,767 --> 00:20:46,800
We'll let you know soon
if there are any updates.

339
00:20:46,867 --> 00:20:50,633
God, please give this to me.

340
00:20:50,700 --> 00:20:53,167
I want to see my daughter.

341
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:06,067
I'm glad Amanda's not here.

342
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:19,600
Your attention, please.

343
00:21:19,667 --> 00:21:21,267
Here's the latest update.

344
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:24,567
Our search and rescue team
in Davao just called.

345
00:21:24,633 --> 00:21:27,167
There will be a delay in
transporting the survivors.

346
00:21:27,233 --> 00:21:29,967
One survivor has
a head injury.

347
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:31,200
Sir, excuse me.

348
00:21:31,267 --> 00:21:34,833
Have you already identified
the survivors?

349
00:21:34,900 --> 00:21:38,567
Sir, has the rescued woman
already been identified?

350
00:21:38,633 --> 00:21:39,600
You're here again?

351
00:21:39,667 --> 00:21:41,500
Can you wait your turn?

352
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:44,433
I talked to him first.
Stop interrupting us!

353
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:47,500
For all you know, your daughter
is already dead.

354
00:21:47,567 --> 00:21:49,233
She's alive!

355
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,133
What made you say so?

356
00:21:51,200 --> 00:21:53,200
A dove brought me
my daughter's message.

357
00:21:53,267 --> 00:21:55,467
Are you happy now?

358
00:22:45,467 --> 00:22:46,600
Mister! Sir!

359
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:47,967
Sir, help us, Sir!

360
00:22:48,033 --> 00:22:49,500
What happened?

361
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:51,400
He had an accident
on the island.

362
00:22:51,467 --> 00:22:53,500
He hit his head somewhere.

363
00:22:53,567 --> 00:22:55,300
He needs to see a doctor,
please!

364
00:22:55,367 --> 00:22:56,733
He's my boyfriend.
Please, Mister.

365
00:22:56,800 --> 00:22:58,967
Bring him to the ambulance
right away.

366
00:22:59,033 --> 00:23:00,633
Go on.
Follow them.

367
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:02,200
Thank you.

368
00:23:05,233 --> 00:23:06,767
Where are the survivors?

369
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:08,167
They're already
in the ambulance.

370
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:09,733
- Why?
- I saw this on the boat.

371
00:23:09,800 --> 00:23:12,000
Maybe it belongs to
one of the survivors.

372
00:23:25,267 --> 00:23:27,067
That's 15 thousand pesos.

373
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:29,500
It will have a 10 percent
interest every month.

374
00:23:29,567 --> 00:23:30,733
I understand.

375
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:32,500
You are your sister's
guarantor, Dindi.

376
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,733
You'll be responsible
if she's delinquent.

377
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:39,367
I will go to Davao right now
and pick up my daughter myself.

378
00:23:39,433 --> 00:23:40,367
Thank you.

379
00:23:40,433 --> 00:23:42,733
Thank you for taking care
of our son.

380
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:45,000
Of course, Auntie.

381
00:23:45,067 --> 00:23:46,533
I will never abandon Red.

382
00:23:46,600 --> 00:23:47,700
You know that.

383
00:23:47,767 --> 00:23:50,533
Didn't Red promise you
that he wouldn't leave you?

384
00:23:50,600 --> 00:23:53,033
He should be here by now
if he's going to save us.

385
00:23:53,100 --> 00:23:58,400
He won't let us wait this long
if he's going to save us.

386
00:23:58,500 --> 00:23:59,767
Yenyen...

387
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:03,233
Sabina, who is Yenyen?
